car.parts

Class CarpartsSet

  • java.lang.Object
    • car.parts.CarpartsSet
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.lang.Iterable<Carpart>

    public class CarpartsSet
extends java.lang.Object
implements java.lang.Iterable<Carpart>
    Represents a set of carParts. In this set it is impossible to add two different parts of the same type. This class does not permit the null element.

      • CarpartsSet

        public CarpartsSet(java.util.Collection<Carpart> collection)
        Creates a new carpartsSet containing the elements of the given collection. If the collection contains multiple parts of the same type, one of these parts will be randomly selected and the other parts will not be contained by this set.

      • CarpartsSet

        public CarpartsSet(Carpart[] array)
        Creates a new carpartsSet containing the elements of the given array. If the array contains multiple parts of the same type, one of these parts will be randomly selected and the other parts will not be contained by this set.
